<p><span style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:black'>On
Nov 23, 2010, at 3:23 PM, &lt;ananda.mudar_at_[hidden]&gt;
&lt;ananda.mudar_at_[hidden]&gt; wrote: <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p><span class=quotelev11><span style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif"'>&gt;
However this error message goes away, if I initialize MPI with threads ie;
MPI_Init_thread(). Can anyone explain this discrepancy? </span></span><span
style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:black'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p><span style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:black'>What
thread level are you invoking MPI_INIT_THREAD with? <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p><span style='font-size:9.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:black'>One
possible reason this could be happening is that the openib BTL is excluding
itself if you use MPI_THREAD_MULTIPLE. The openib BTL is the entity that is
responsible for the fork warning -- if it's not being used, then no warning is
issued because there is no problem with forking. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

